
[1]reminiscence

   REMINIS'CENCE, n. [L. reminiscens, reminiscor, Gr. See Memory.]

   1. That faculty of the mind by which ideas formerly received into it,
   but forgotten, are recalled or revived in the memory.

   2. Recollection; recovery of ideas that had escaped from the memory.
